# The native-OpenAPI snapshot test (ergo-api/tests/openapi_native_snapshot.rs)
# byte-compares this fixture against the generated spec, which is always
# LF. Without this, Windows autocrlf rewrites the fixture to CRLF on
# checkout and the comparison fails locally even though the committed
# bytes are correct. Pin it to LF so the snapshot is platform-stable.
ergo-api/tests/fixtures/openapi_native.yaml text eol=lf
ergo-api/tests/fixtures/openapi_v1.yaml text eol=lf

# test-vectors are byte-exact oracle artifacts (JVM-oracle-captured corpus
# sources, verdict/seed JSON, wire hex). EOL conversion must never touch them:
# on Windows, autocrlf CRLF-rewrites the .es corpus at checkout, shifting the
# parser's line:col positions against the committed oracle verdicts
# (corpus_verdict_parity fails with position-only divergences). -text disables
# all conversion so every OS sees the committed bytes verbatim.
test-vectors/** -text
